                <article id="content_0_newslandingpage_main_2_twocolumnleftfocus_left_0_lvStoriesRight_ctrl0_article2" class="editors-picks-type01" data-vr-contentbox="">
                    <h2 class="m">
                        <a id="content_0_newslandingpage_main_2_twocolumnleftfocus_left_0_lvStoriesRight_ctrl0_storyRight_headlineLink" href="http://www.thestar.com.my/Business/Business-News/2013/08/28/Petronas-Says-No-Deal-With-Brazils-OGX-Until-Debt-Restructured.aspx"> Petronas Says No Deal With Brazil's OGX Until Debt Restructured</a>
                    </h2>
                    <p>RIO DE JANEIRO/KUALA LUMPUR: Petroliam Nasional Bhd, the Malaysian state oil company, said a final agreement to buy a stake in an oil field owned by Brazil's OGX Petróleo e Gas Participações SA is being held up by the completion of OGX's debt restructuring plan.</p>
                </article>
            
                <article id="content_0_newslandingpage_main_2_twocolumnleftfocus_left_0_lvStoriesRight_ctrl1_article2" class="editors-picks-type01" data-vr-contentbox="">

                        <a id="content_0_newslandingpage_main_2_twocolumnleftfocus_left_0_lvStoriesRight_ctrl1_storyRight_headlineLink" href="http://www.thestar.com.my/Business/Business-News/2013/08/28/OGX-Shares-Slide-As-It-Drops-License-Bids-Petronas-Holds-Up-Deal.aspx"> OGX Shares Slide As It Drops License Bids, Petronas Holds Up Deal</a>
                    </h2>
                    <p>RIO DE JANEIRO/KUALA LUMPUR: Shares of OGX Petróleo e Gas Participações SA slid 14.8 percent on Tuesday as the troubled oil producer abandoned its plan to purchase several oil exploration licenses and its venture with the Malaysian state oil company appeared to be in serious trouble.</p>
                </article>
